cs.DB, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.DL, cs.CY 

The paper discusses the need for the database research community to broaden its focus to include online data, which suggests a strong connection to the sub-category of cs.DB (Database). The paper also emphasizes the importance of analyzing and presenting online data, which aligns with the sub-categories of cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper mentions the need to rethink fundamental assumptions in light of technology shifts, which could relate to the sub-categories of cs.DL (Digital Libraries) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
